venue.name: Ya Hua Bak Kut Teh Eating House
Ya Hua Bak Kut Teh Eating House

tip.text: Yong tau foo is not very good. Choice is so limited and soup taste artificial!
Try the fried Bee Hoon, it's quite nice but a little expensive. I think it's only available at the IHQ. Coffee is a good local choice!
If you feel like eating Indian food, you can try stall no 79 Faizur. They serve good mutton soup although can be a tad salty at times, and light, tasty and not too oily fried Bee Hoon chicken.
The set lunches with egg for sweet and sour pork rice and ginger onion chicken rice are value for money and taste not bad!
